<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idbfdfcff0-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s15096"><num value="15096">§ 15096.</num><heading> Authorized activities</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="idbfdfcff1-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s15096/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> In general</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">A State that receives a grant under <ref href="/us/usc/t42/s15093">section 15093 of this title</ref> shall use the funds made available through the grant to carry out systems change activities that accomplish the purposes of this subchapter.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="idbfdfcff2-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s15096/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Special rule</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">In carrying out activities authorized under this subchapter, a State shall ensure that such activities address the needs of families of children with disabilities from unserved or underserved populations.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="idbfdfcff3-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa">(<ref href="/us/pl/106/402/tII/s207">Pub. L. 106–402, title II, § 207</ref>, <date date="2000-10-30">Oct. 30, 2000</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/114/1732">114 Stat. 1732</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
